TY  - JOUR
T1  - Research Notes
AU  - Nelson, Nels E.
Y1  - 1979/12/01
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255816
DO  - 10.5465/255816
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 810
EP  - 815
VL  - 22
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article focuses on the research works of Ronan and L. Sayles about labor relations concerning technology and the grievance rates of working groups. The author presents and attempts to correct several shortcomings Ronan's study. The study attempts to classify the grievance rates of groups. Also included are a number of hypotheses on the working group that will have the lowest and highest level of grievance activity. According to the author, when designing work processes, employers should take into consideration the impact technology will have on the employee grievance process.
AB  - The article focuses on the research works of Ronan and L. Sayles about labor relations concerning technology and the grievance rates of working groups. The author presents and attempts to correct several shortcomings Ronan's study. The study attempts to classify the grievance rates of groups. Also included are a number of hypotheses on the working group that will have the lowest and highest level of grievance activity. According to the author, when designing work processes, employers should take into consideration the impact technology will have on the employee grievance process.
