TY  - JOUR
T1  - Understanding Reorganizations of Divisionalized Companies
AU  - Allen, Stephen A.
Y1  - 1979/12/01
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255807
DO  - 10.5465/255807
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 641
EP  - 671
VL  - 22
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This paper reports the results of a longitudinal study of company-wide reorganizations in divisionalized companies. Characteristics, beliefs, and strategies of top management groups were found to be fully as important as contextual factors in predicting organizational choices. Constellations of contextual factors seem to establish a range of feasible options for reorganization within which top management usually has considerable scope for choice.
AB  - This paper reports the results of a longitudinal study of company-wide reorganizations in divisionalized companies. Characteristics, beliefs, and strategies of top management groups were found to be fully as important as contextual factors in predicting organizational choices. Constellations of contextual factors seem to establish a range of feasible options for reorganization within which top management usually has considerable scope for choice.
