T1  - Judgmental Decisions: A Study of Interactions Among Group Membership, Group Functioning, and the Decision Situation
AU  - Stumpf, Stephen A.
AU  - Freedman, Richard D.
AU  - Zand, Dale E.
Y1  - 1979/12/01
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255813
DO  - 10.5465/255813
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 765
EP  - 782
VL  - 22
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In an experimental investigation of judgmental decision making (JDM) strong interactions are found among membership types (experts, representatives, coworkers), group functioning (interacting, nominal), and six decision situations. The findings suggest that meta-decisions made when forming a JDM group affect the effectiveness of decisions, and they imply limitations in generalizing prior research.
AB  - In an experimental investigation of judgmental decision making (JDM) strong interactions are found among membership types (experts, representatives, coworkers), group functioning (interacting, nominal), and six decision situations. The findings suggest that meta-decisions made when forming a JDM group affect the effectiveness of decisions, and they imply limitations in generalizing prior research.
